-- PRESS DIGEST - China - July 18
-- By Shanghai Newsroom
-- Thu Jul 17, 2014 10:23PM EDT
-- None



July 18 (Reuters) - Chinese newspapers available in Beijing and Shanghai carried the following stories on Friday. Reuters has not checked the stories and does not vouch for their accuracy.

SECURITIES TIMES - In the first half of the year, 117 Chinese brokerages made a combined net profit of 32.3 billion yuan ($5.21 billion). This was higher than the 24.5 billion yuan net profit from 114 brokerages in the same period in 2013, according to figures from the Securities Association of China.   CHINA DAILY - The new set of rules on the use of vehicles by government officials is one of a series of measures against extravagancy and corruption that threaten to trigger public discontent, China Daily said in an editorial.  21st CENTURY BUSINESS HERALD - Chen Zhenggao, head of Ministry of Housing and Urban-Rural Development, said China's real estate policy over the next six months is to digest the inventory of unsold houses, strengthen structural adjustment and improve facilities around new properties.